  <description type="morphology">Caudices simple, 1–1.5 cm diam.  Leaves: rosettes 6–10(–25)-leaved; blade shiny green, often with maroon abaxially, ovate to elliptic, 2–5 × 1.5–2.5 cm, apex acute to acuminate, surfaces not farinose, not glaucous.  Inflorescences: floral shoots 5–15-leaved, 4–15 cm; cincinni 3+, 3–5-flowered, 1–3 cm.  Petals bright yellow, often marked with red, 10–14 × 2.5–3.5 mm.  2n = 34.</description>
